        <name><![CDATA[Grandma B's]]></name>
        <description>Tony had a sandwich and fries with Sala Udin, Hill District community leader, former councilman.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.9705415,40.4486945,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Kelly's Bar & Lounge]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had beer, kielbasa, sauerkraut, pierogies, and mac & cheese with wrestlers Brittany Baker and Adam Cole]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.9243914,40.4598916,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Jozsa Corner</name>
        <description><![CDATA["More like a house party with food," than a restaurant, says Tony. They had chicken paprikash, lángos (Hungarian fried bread), kolbasz (Hungarian sausage), cucumber salad.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.944802,40.411122,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
