          <coordinates>
            -79.9252858,40.4600402,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Hidy's Cafe]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony met with filmmaker Tony Buba to have drinks and discuss the economy of Braddock's blue collar neighborhood.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.8772235,40.4078349,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Superior Motors</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with John Fetterman, mayor of Braddock; Gisele Fetterman, who runs a nonprofit to help those in need in their community; Franco Harris, four-time Super Bowl champion; and Chef Kevin Sousa, restaurateur behind Superior Motors. They had Lake Erie walleye pike, new potatoes, fish cracklin, and fresh herbs; beef short ribs on milkweed buds and overwintered sunchoke chips; wine.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.8604611,40.3977278,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>New Alexandria Lions Club Demolition Derby</name>
        <description>Tony had beer with Brooke Davis, demolition driver, and Chris Quenzler Jr., mechanic</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1879-FFD600</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -79.4399493,40.3926944,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Galle Face Green</name>
        <description><![CDATA["This is our Central Park," Dharshan Munidasa says (a chef and TV personality). Tony and Dharshan had street food here.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            79.847008,6.9185844,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Nelum Kole Restaurant</name>
        <description>Tony had lunch at this local rice and curry joint with Kumar Lopez, CEO of Sri Lanka Press Institute, a news trade organization. They had chicken curry, spicy potatoes, beets, and rice.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            79.8495705,6.9106019,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
