      <Placemark>
        <name>Revel</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony ate at this Korean restaurant with John Cook and Todd Bishop, co-founders of tech news website GeekWire. They had: "cilantro noodles with yu choy, and thinly sliced flat iron steak; kimchi pancakes with braised pork belly and bean sprouts; marinated short rib rice bowl with house sambal daikon, kimchi, and egg; and short rib dumplings topped with pickled shallot and scallion salad."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.3541234,47.6520315,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Emerald Haze Cannabis Emporium</name>
        <description>Tony went to this weed dispensary to buy some pot, since it is legal in the state of Washington</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1684-097138</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.1655331,47.5038381,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Hollingsworth Cannabis Company</name>
        <description>A marijuana farm that supplies some of the dispensaries</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1566-097138</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.222517,47.26112,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Mamnoon</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had a meal with the Hollingsworths, from the cannabis farm. They had Lebanese food here: "baharat spiced beef and lamb kabobs, fried cauliflower with tahini, a summer fatteh with local squash and charred tomatoes topped with sizzling brown butter and pine nuts; sweet and sour rice wrapped in grape leaves; hummus."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.327591,47.614385,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Modernist Cuisine</name>
        <description>Tony visited this cooking lab and met with Nathan Myhrvold, author of a book Modernist Cuisine. They had baba au rhum in a jar, and a bagel.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-F57C00</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.1488803,47.5805266,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Vashon Island</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony ate with local chefs. They had a "clam bake with dungeness crab, spot prawns, corn, and potatoes, covered in kelp and steamed together under burlap."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.4862839,47.4229122,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Taylor Shellfish Oyster Bar</name>
        <description>Tony ate with a group. They had lots of oysters; flash-fried whole local smelt served with pepperoncini sambal aioli; local dungeness crab, chilled and cooked with pickled ginger sauce.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.3326444,47.5988278,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[North Star Diner & Shanghai Room]]></name>
        <description>Tony met with retired Seattle homicide detective Mike Ciesynski to discuss serial killers. They ordered food from North Star Diner: crab, bacon, and melted cheese sandwich</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.3550185,47.692278,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Ocho</name>
        <description>Tony met with rock star Mark Lanegan (from Queens of the Stone Age, and also the person who wrote the theme show of Parts Unknown). They had tapas and drinks.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.3873675,47.6685471,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Ricciolandia</name>
        <description>Tony had uni pasta and beer.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            17.4447133,40.8543955,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Palazzo Margherita Hotel</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with Francis Ford Coppola. They had lampascioni, or scored and fried hyacinth bulbs; braciole di cotenna, or stuffed pig skin rolls; lamb’s head casserole, fresh fruit, assorted wines.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-AFB42B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            16.6871911,40.4074375,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Masseria Spina Resort</name>
        <description>Tony had a pasta dinner here with Asia Argento.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            17.2692319,40.9643026,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Matera</name>
        <description>A cave city that predates the Greek and Roman empires. Tony visited the city with Asia Argento. It used to be where the outcasts were sent, until Hollywood came to make movies. Now there are tourists and AirBnBs.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            16.6043199,40.666379,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
