    <Folder>
      <name>Season 11</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Meal with locals</name>
        <description>Tony had dinner with the McKinney family, “a typical expression of hard-scrabble Appalachian practicality,” combined with “Neapolitan roots”: spaghetti pizza, chicken stew with peas and onions, pumpkin pie cake.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1603-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -81.5845513,37.4328913,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Mount View High School</name>
        <description>Tony visited this high school where football is life. Tony attends the pre-game meal of ribs, baked potatoes, and chicken. </description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1579-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -81.5427754,37.4038436,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Coffee Shop</name>
        <description>Tony had biscuits with gravy and fried eggs with journalist Nick Mullins and documentarian Elaine McMillion Sheldon.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -81.6875701,37.3019998,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Brooksrun Mining Co</name>
        <description>Tony ate bear meat in a coal mine with miners.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1627-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -81.5758589,37.4395533,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>King Knob Motorsports Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony visited this off road park of mud and machines (ATVs, motorbikes). On the menu: "frog legs, snapping-turtle patties, catfish (barbecued and fried), smoked bass."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1661-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -80.1243297,39.1881198,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Keith's Bar & Grille]]></name>
        <description>Tony had a beer with a Trump supporter to try to understand why they voted for him.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1879-FFD600</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -81.8719467,37.7312268,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lost Creek Farm</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had a meal with Mike Costello and Amy Dawson, chefs and owners of Lost Creek Farm.<br>They had desperation pie,  pawpaw ice cream with candied wildflowers, buttermilk-poached trout with fresh-picked rhubarb, sweet-corn chowder, buttermilk-fried rabbit with fresh maple syrup, venison with a chicory-root rub, chanterelle mushrooms, and wild pears.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -80.3125819,39.1209886,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bar Arocena</name>
        <description>Unofficial sandwich of Uruguay: the Chivito: a steak, ham, bacon, cheese, hard boiled egg, mayo, and garnishes.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.0565108,-34.8898524,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Jacinto</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had dinner with chef and owner Lucía Soria and Nacho. They had "homemade gnocchi with mushrooms and pumpkin; prawns with avocado, apple, and wasabi; beef tartare with quail egg."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.2079674,-34.9084061,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Escaramuza Libros</name>
        <description>Tony had lunch with journalist Carina Novarese. They had homemade sausage with roasted turnip and fermented vegetables, beet quiche.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.1711583,-34.9065361,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bar Las Flores</name>
        <description>Tony had pizza with the Hablan por la Espalda bandmates. They had pizza a caballo, or “a bizarro stoner hybrid topped with thin chickpea flatbread”</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1651-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.1717945,-34.9078994,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Cantina del Vigía</name>
        <description>Tony and friends ate a feast of empanadas with corn and shredded, slow-cooked beef; goat cheese and spinach croquettes; fried fish; provoleta (bubbling cheese that “puffs up and inflates on the plate”); whole roasted suckling wild boar; whole roasted fish; beef milanesa covered in tomato sauce, ham, and shredded cheese.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -54.9607478,-34.910493,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Las Nenas Steak House</name>
        <description>Tony, Nacho, and Diego went to this drive through to have skirt steak and ribeye, french fries, blood sausages, and beer..</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -54.9370442,-34.9383809,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Parador La Huella</name>
        <description>Tony ate with the owners of this place. They had whole fish baked in salt, rib-eye steak, flank steak, suckling pig.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -54.6337545,-34.8422344,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Chafe's Landing Restaurant]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had fish & chips with Dale Jarvis, Intangible Cultural Heritage Development Officer for the Heritage Foundation of Newfoundland and Labrador.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -52.7116714,47.4639652,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Red Indian Lake</name>
        <description>Tony went with a group of chefs to a place up near the lake to eat some hearty cod stew, various terrines (duck, rabbit, guinea hen, boar), jellied foie gras, fire-roasted moose shoulder and leg, ribs braised with red wine, local boletus, and chanterelle mushrooms.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1765-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.8704291,48.7258121,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Raymonds Restaurant</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony, Fred Morin, and Dave McMillan had a seafood tower of "razor clams, snow crab, mussels, capelin, whelks, and sea urchin," boquerones; scallop crudo with smoked roe; tuna prepared with berries; heart of caribou tartare with alder and chanterelle mushrooms; charred whelk with crispy cod sounds (fried fish bladders); cod filet with cod liver canelé, partridge profiteroles, Jiggs dinner (a boiled dish of meat and root veggies) reinvented as a pasta dish, chanterelle ice cream.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -52.7040365,47.5667051,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Saint Pierre and Miquelon</name>
        <description>Tony, Fred, and Dave went to this island to visit Maïté Legasse, home cook and director of Ma P’tite Cocotte. They had sea urchin pâté, stuffed squid over rice, braised halibut, local cheese, tart with local baked apples and blackberries.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1603-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -56.3159,46.8852,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Big R Restaurant</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony and a group of chefs had fried bologna which Tony called "awesome," fried clam strips, liver and onions, pan-fried cod tongues, Jiggs dinner, french fries.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -52.7383912,47.5461281,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Jack Axes</name>
        <description>Tony, Fred, and Dave threw axes and had a cheese plate, an assortment of patés, and pickled pork tongue.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1802-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -52.7202152,47.5649763,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Christian's Bar]]></name>
        <description>Tony met with chefs Fred Morin and Dave McMillan. They had a fried bologna cube and Newfoundland‘s very own Screech Rum.</description>
