      <Placemark>
        <name>Nagorno-Karabakh</name>
        <description>Tony camped out in the wilderness with Tigran Grigoryan, a war veteran and aspiring politician; Tatul Hakobyan, a journalist; Saro Saryan, an Armenian born in Azerbaijan who fled during the war. They had  jingalov hats, or “lavash bread stuffed with greens and onions before being toasted atop a cast-iron sheet” and Armenian barbecue covered in fennel and fresh herbs</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1765-0288D1</styleUrl>
