      <Placemark>
        <name>Sun Hing Restaurant</name>
        <description>Tony went for dim sum with Janice Lau and Jason Cheung, members of Hong Kong punk band David Boring.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            114.1282358,22.2829656,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Happy Paradise</name>
        <description>Tony had dinner with Jenny Suen, feng shui master Thierry Chow, and chef May Chow. They had sourdough chicken-fat egg waffle with Taiwanese bottarga; sauteed prawns with pan-roasted pumpkin, dried shrimp roe, and prawn oil; tea-smoked pigeon; Hakka-style chicken; and pig brain with burnt-pear vinaigrette.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            114.1518692,22.282691,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lau Sum Kee Noodle</name>
        <description>Tony had lunch with Douglas Young, founder of Goods of Desire. They had prawn-roe noodles.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            114.1630699,22.3322331,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Domke Nino Fleischerei</name>
        <description>Tony met with Frank Künster, legendary Berlin bouncer. They had pork schnitzel with brown gravy and boulette (pork meatballs). They discussed the nightclub scene in Berlin.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
