      <Placemark>
        <name>Lewa Wildlife Conservancy</name>
        <description>Tony and Kamau visited this conservancy to view the animals. They saw a giraffe, termite mounds, zebras, an ostrich, an elephant, a rhino, and some lions. They then had a breakfast of scrambled eggs and toast with Mike Watson, CEO of the conservancy; Faith Riunga, education officer of the conservancy; Wanjiku Kinuthia, communications officer of the conservancy; Tom Lalampaa, CEO of Northern Rangelands Trust</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.4408517,0.2253854,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Il Ngwesi Community</name>
        <description>Tony and Kamau met with Masai chief Jonathan Kip and Masai elder Lela Kinyaga to have a meal in a Masai village. They had cow’s blood mixed with milk, grilled meat, and rice.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.3613533,0.342868,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
